President Biden welcomed a group of scientists and researchers to the White House to honor their outstanding contributions to science and technology. In his remarks, he emphasized the importance of investing in science and research to drive innovation and improve the well-being of the nation and the world. He highlighted the achievements of the honorees, ranging from advancements in clean energy and agriculture to breakthroughs in neurobiology and disease treatment. The President also discussed his administration's commitment to science, including the fight against cancer and the promotion of diversity in STEM fields. He concluded by expressing his belief in the limitless possibilities that America can achieve through scientific progress.